snippet.textDisplay:
I want to mention here that our National Anthem is totally written in Persian Language not in Urdu.  Urdu is our National Language and is mixture of Hindi, Persian, Arabic and also Punjabi. 
An interesting fact regarding our anthem i.e. its was composed before it had to be written. It was because Shah-e-Iran visited Pakistan in early 1950, he requested to play music/tone/composition of Pakistan National Anthem on his welcome. At that time our anthem was not written and approved by Government officially. Time was short enough to write anthem then compose it afterwards. Therefore its music was composed first. After Shah visit to Pakistan, the copies of music/tone/composition was sent to Poets, writers and dramatists to write Pakistan National Anthem. This honour goes to Hafeez Jalandhari to write Pakistan National Anthem.
